                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.11241 Manchuria/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-10T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 10, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>156. Your 244, June 6, 1 p.m. Department authorizes Legation to instruct
                    Ballantine as suggested in the penultimate paragraph of your telegram. The
                    Department will await with interest a report of Ballantine’s informal
                    discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
